CatDescriptText: Mrs. James Starks, housewife, Homewood, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1961, pg. 7 with question: "Do you think that men should marry women within their own age bracket (not over fiver years difference) or do you approve of 'May and December' marriages?" answer reads: "That depends on how many things the two have in common. I'm happily married and my husband is a little older than I..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. James Starks wearing dark knitted cardigan, standing in front of ribbed metal wall
